Just a playground. Not for production use.

How to try it:
install rubygem-ruby-augeas from OBS
    sudo zypper ar http://download.opensuse.org/repositories/devel:/languages:/ruby:/extensions/openSUSE_11.4/ rubyext
    sudo zypper in rubygem-ruby-augeas
install rubygem-open4
    sudo zypper in rubygem-open4
sudo rake install
cd kerberos-client-api
ruby kerberos_conf


How to obtain permission for common user:
  su
  mkdir -p /etc/polkit-1/localauthority/50.local.d
  mv doc/org.opensuse.systemagents.pkla /etc/polkit-1/localauthority/50.local.d
#replace <yourcooluser> with real user in /etc/polkit-1/localauthority/org.opensuse.systemagents.pkla
